<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 07 at 3:39PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Areas of Snow Diminishing This Evening...
Areas of snow and fog in the Gallatin Valley are reducing
visibility to a half mile or less at times. Additional snow
accumulation of an inch will be possible through the evening,
especially in the Gallatin Gateway area. After skies clear out
late tonight, fog may develop for the Monday morning commute.</description>
